OL,6,F"This is not acceptable, and I
OL,7,Funreservedly apologise to the families
OL,8,Fof victims on behalf of the NHS and
OL,9,Fthe organisations involved in
OL,10,Fdelivering care to Valdo Calocane
OL,11,Fbefore this incident took place."
OL,13,FClaire Murdoch, NHS England's national
OL,14,Fmental health director, said: "It is
OL,15,Fclear there were failings in the care
OL,16,Fprovided to Valdo Calocane, which is
OL,17,Fwhy the trust responsible was placed
OL,18,Fin our highest oversight and support
OL,19,Fprogramme, which has seen them
OL,20,Foverhaul their risk assessment
OL,21,Fprocesses.
